SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 634
By Johnson
A RESOLUTION to confirm the appointment of Dr. Phil Roe to the
state university board of Austin Peay State
University.
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-101, provides for the governance
of Austin Peay State University by a state university board; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-201, provides that the governor
shall appoint six members to the state university board of Austin Peay State University; and
WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-201, further provides that at least
three of the gubernatorial appointees shall be alumni of the institution for which they are serving;
and
WHEREAS, Governor Bill Lee has appointed Dr. Phil Roe to the state university board of
Austin Peay State University for a term that will expire on June 30, 2031; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Phil Roe proudly represented Tennessee's First District in the U.S.
Congress for six terms (2009-2021); and
WHEREAS, a veteran of the U.S. Army Medical Corps, Dr. Roe was a stalwart
champion of our nation's veterans during his twelve-year tenure in Congress, in addition to
serving as co-chair of the House GOP Doctors Caucus; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Roe also gave back to his community through his service as the Mayor
of Johnson City (2007-2009) and as a medical practitioner in Johnson City, delivering nearly
5,000 babies; and
WHEREAS, a native of Clarksville, Dr. Roe earned a degree in biology with a minor in
chemistry from Austin Peay State University and earned his medical degree from the University
of Tennessee; and
SJR0634
011638
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-8-201, provides that each member
appointed by the governor to the state university board of Austin Peay State University shall be
subject to confirmation by the senate and the house of representatives; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we hereby confirm the appointment of Dr. Phil Roe
to the state university board of Austin Peay State University for a term that will expire on June
30, 2031.
